fulltitle: Poisoning the Press: Richard Nixon vs. Journalist Jack Anderson
title: Poisoning the Press: Richard Nixon vs. Journalist Jack Anderson
_filename: _Poisoning the Press - Richard Nixon vs. Journalist Jack Anderson.mp4
description:
October 6, 2010 | Mark Feldstein examines the feud between President Richard Nixon and investigative journalist Jack Anderson, a harsh critic of the president throughout his career. Mr. Feldstein recounts Jack Anderson’s means of acquiring information about the Nixon administration, from poring over classified documents to sorting through garbage, and the administration’s nefarious plans to hurt the journalist. Mark Feldstein presented his book at King’s English Bookshop in Salt Lake City, Utah.
